						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the compound of the Chennakēśavasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>DĒVARĀYA (II).</p>						

						<p>1430 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in the cyclic year Savumya (Saumya), Chaitra, śu. 30. Wednesday. On the basis of the internal evidences, the dates correspond to 1430 A.D., April 3, the week day being Monday.</p>						

						<p>It records the gift of • • • • • garden and one <hi rend="italic">tūmu</hi> of land for maintaining the offerings to the god Chennakēśava situated at Kōḍūru by <hi rend="italic">mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> Avubhaladēva mahārāja. It is stated that the chief got Kōḍūru as <hi rend="italic">nāyankara</hi> from the king Dēvarāya, situated in the territorial division Mulikinānḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
